  "description": "To fell one Cypress, T42 on TPO 114",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "This mature Cypress tree makes a significant contribution to the visual amenity and arboreal character of this local area. The tree is considered to have a Moderate amenity value.",
    "The applicant is alleging that the damage to the righthand side of their property has been caused by the Cypress and as a result they wish to remove the tree.",
    "Applications to remove a protected tree due to suspected structural damage must be supported by relevant technical evidence which demonstrates 'beyond reasonable doubt' that any alleged structural damage has been caused by the implicated tree. Such evidence would usually include (but not be limited to):",
    "1. Root testing - to show that roots of the implicated tree have been found below the area of damage; and",
    "2. Crack / Level monitoring date - to demonstrate that the crack damage / building movement is seasonal and cyclical (that is, cracks open during the drier summer months and close during the winter months - or in the case of level monitoring, the",
    "The removal of deadwood, dangerous / hanging branches and ivy:  This does not require the formal consent of the Council."
